# E. Determination of kuncat for Kemp elimination of various benzisoxazoles

kuncat was determined as a function of buffer concentration at $\mathrm { p H } ~ 7 . 2 5$ at $2 5 \mathrm { { ^ \circ C } }$ , and extrapolated to zero buffer concentration. Non-enzymatic elimination was followed in Hepes $\mathrm { p H } ~ 7 . 2 5$ (10, 25, 50, 75, 100mM) by monitoring the absorbance. For 5- nitrobenzisoxazole and 5,7-dichlorobenzisoxazole, the plots were fit to the equation: OD $= \mathrm { C \ ( 1 { - } e ^ { - \mathrm { k t } } ) }$ , where OD is the absorbance, C is a constant, $\mathrm { k }$ is the ${ \mathrm { k } } _ { \mathrm { u n c a t : } }$ , and $\mathrm { \Delta t }$ is time in minutes. For 6-chloro and 5-fluorobenzisoxazole, the initial linear stage of elimination was monitored. The kinetics of elimination at various buffer concentrations are represented at Fig. S19-S22. The ${ \bf k } _ { \mathrm { u n c a t } }$ values for zero buffer concentration were obtained by plotting the ${ \bf k } _ { \mathrm { u n c a t } }$ values obtained for various Hepes concentrations and extrapolating to $0 \mathrm { m M }$ Hepes (Fig. S23). The obtained ${ \bf k } _ { \mathrm { u n c a t } }$ values are summarized in Table S9.

Table S9. ${ \bf k } _ { \mathrm { u n c a t } }$ values for elimination of various benzisoxazoles.

