# F. Synthesis and characterization of substrates and inhibitors

Benzisoxazole, benzotriazole, and 6-chlorobenzotriazole were purchased from Sigma-Aldrich. 5-nitrobenzotriazole was purchased from Matrix Organics. 5-nitrobenzisoxazole was prepared by nitration of benzisoxazole (19). All the other benzisoxazoles were prepared from corresponding salicylaldehydes by the procedure of Kemp (20). $p K _ { a } ^ { L G }$ values of the salicylonitriles were obtained from the literature (Table S10).

# 5-nitro benzisoxazole (by procedure of Hollfelder (21)

1,2 benzisoxazole (1gr) was dissolved in $\mathrm { H } _ { 2 } \mathrm { S O } _ { 4 } ~ 9 8 \%$ (4ml) at $0 \%$ . A mixture of $9 8 \%$ $\mathrm { H } _ { 2 } \mathrm { S O } _ { 4 }$ $( 0 . 2 2 \mathrm { m l } )$ and $70 \%$ $\mathrm { H N O } _ { 3 }$ $( 0 . 5 2 \mathrm { m l } )$ ) was added slowly, the reaction was stirred 30 min at RT and then poured onto ice-water mixture $( 2 0 \mathrm { m l } )$ . The suspension was vacuumfiltered, and the precipitate was washed with ethanol, dried on vacuum and lyophilized. Yield – $5 4 0 \mathrm { m g }$ $( 3 9 \% )$ . 1 HNMR (250MHz, $\mathrm { C D C l } _ { 3 }$ ): %(ppm): 7.74-7.78(d,1H), 8.49 - 8.54(dd, 1H), 8.73 (d, 1H), 8.91(s, 1H).

# 5-chlorobenzisoxazole (by procedure of Casey (20))

5-chlorosalicylaldehyde (0.5gr, 3.2mmol) was dissolved in ethanol. Hydroxylammonium O-sulfonate $( 0 . 5 \mathrm { g r } )$ was added, and the mixture was stirred $1 0 \mathrm { { m i n } }$ at RT. Then, $1 5 \mathrm { m l }$ DCM was added, and the reaction was cooled at $4 \mathrm { { } ^ { \circ } C }$ . Solution of $\mathrm { N a H C O } _ { 3 }$ was added $( 0 . 7 5 \mathrm { g r / 7 m l \ H _ { 2 } O ) }$ , and the reaction mixture was mixed for $3 0 \mathrm { { m i n } }$ at RT. After fractions separation, the aqueous fraction was extracted with 3 times with DCM. The DCM fractions were combined, dried with ${ \mathrm { N a } } _ { 2 } { \mathrm { S O } } _ { 4 }$ , filtered and evaporated. The residue was purified by flash chromatography (silica 60, $2 \%$ MeOH in DCM).
5-fluoro benzisoxazole: 1 HNMR (250MHz, $\mathrm { C D C l } _ { 3 }$ ): %(ppm): 7.15-7.35(m,2H), 7.45- 7.55(m, 1H), 8.15 (s, 1H). ESI-MS: $\mathrm { m } / z$ : 137 [M]  .
5-nitro 6-chloro benzisoxazole: 1 HNMR (250MHz, $\mathrm { C D C l } _ { 3 }$ ): %(ppm): 7.83(s,1H), 8.33(s, 1H), 8.83 (s, 1H). ESI-MS: m/z: 198 [M]  .
5,7 dichloro benzisoxazole: 1 HNMR (250MHz, CDCl3): %(ppm): 7.55(d, 1H), 7.65(d, 1H), 8.70(s, 1H). ESI-MS: m/z: 187 [M]  .
