# 5,7 dichlorobenzotriazole and 5-nitro 6-chlorobenzotriazole (by procedure of Damschroder and Peterson (22))

Briefly, 3,5-dichlorophenylenediamine (3mmol, $5 3 0 \mathrm { m g }$ ), glacial acetic acid $\left( \sim 1 \mathrm { m l } \right)$ and water $( \sim 3 \mathrm { m l } )$ were placed in a flask, and the mixture was heated till dissolved and put on ice. Cold solution of sodium nitrite $\lvert 3 . 3 \mathrm { m m o l } { = } 0 . 2 9 \mathrm { g r } / 0 . 4 \mathrm { m l }$ water) was added at once, and the ice bath was removed. The mixture was stirred slowly $1 \mathrm { h } / \mathrm { R T }$ and 3h in ice bath, and the solid was collected on a Buchner funnel, washed with cold water and recrystallized from methanol. 5,7 dichlorobenzotriazole - ESI-MS: $\mathrm { m } / z$ : 187.8 $\left[ \mathrm { M } { + } 1 \right]$ -

